Overview
--------

This repository contains scripts for managing various server configurations on
HP Cloud Services (HPCS). You'll need an HPCS account. You can get one here:
https://www.hpcloud.com/

Prerequisites
-------------

You'll need a Python command line utility called `nova`. You can install it on
a Debian system like this:

    sudo apt-get install python-nova

You'll also need to have the following Perl modules installed:

    - YAML::XS
    - JSON::XS

Setup
-----

Copy the `hpcs` directory to `~/.hpcs` like this:

    cp -r ./hpcs ~/.hpcs

and then edit the files in `~/.hpcs` appropriately.
